$ SQL Server: sys.databases
@ sys.databases

{ Database level options #mssql-db-level-options

  Some options can apparently set with a default for each database:
  
  gh|about-MSSQL|/administration/schemas/sys/objects/views/databases/options.sql||

  These options can then be overwritten with the → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/statements/set[`set` statement].

}

sa:

  → development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/database

  → development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/schemas/sys
